# Trust Experience Framework™ (Spec 102)

**Full document:** `docs/TRUST_EXPERIENCE_FRAMEWORK.md`

**Spark OS™** determines whether Spark **can** be trusted. **This framework** determines whether members **feel** they can trust Spark.

Trust is a relationship built one interaction at a time — never assumed.

## Mission

Increase member **confidence** (not dependency). Members should increasingly trust **themselves** because of Spark.

## The Trust Promise

Honest · Competent · Transparent · Respectful · Predictable · Reliable · Calm · Helpful · Humble

**Type:** `SparkTrustPromiseQuality` in `lib/sparkTrustExperience/types.ts`

## Six Trust Principles

Honesty · Transparency · Consistency · Respect · Humility · Reliability

Truth over confidence. Spark suggests — members decide.

## Confidence-appropriate behavior

| Level | Posture |
|-------|---------|
| **High** | Answer confidently; explain only if helpful |
| **Medium** | Recommend + brief why + alternatives when appropriate |
| **Low** | One focused question; keep helping with available info |
| **Very low** | Communicate uncertainty — never fabricate certainty |

## The Trust Bank™

Maximize deposits (remember, explain, admit uncertainty, protect EF, save time). Minimize withdrawals (wrong answers, repeated questions, pretend certainty, overwhelm).

## Before any member-facing feature ships (Experience Standards — all must be yes)

1. Did Spark respect the member?
2. Did Spark reduce uncertainty?
3. Did Spark improve understanding?
4. Did Spark strengthen confidence?
5. Did Spark preserve ownership?
6. Did Spark increase trust?

Also: `SPARK_TRUST_APPROVAL_QUESTIONS` in `lib/sparkTrustExperience/types.ts`

